    "description_long": "This object is a collection of ten grave markers arranged in a row, each with distinct shapes and sizes, typical of a small graveyard or cemetery section. The markers include a variety of forms such as crosses, obelisks, and traditional headstones, all appearing to be made from weathered stone with dark, aged textures. Some markers feature cross motifs, while others are simple rectangular or arched slabs, and one is a tall, slender obelisk with a cross at the top. The surfaces are rough and matte, with visible signs of wear and discoloration, suggesting exposure to the elements over time. The color palette is dominated by dark grays and muted browns, enhancing the somber, historical atmosphere. No visible inscriptions or detailed engravings can be discerned from the images, and there are no mausoleums or gates present.",
